12:27.989 --> 12:31.641
-That's not my dad.
-Yeah, it kind of was.

12:31.810 --> 12:32.917
Yeah.

12:33.086 --> 12:35.069
Your daddy would have
a few drinks occasionally

12:35.163 --> 12:36.254
and become remorseful,

12:36.423 --> 12:39.482
and he called me and insists
the kids be included

12:39.534 --> 12:42.318
and then later he would
reinstate the original will

12:42.487 --> 12:44.153
-with no extramarital children.
-ROSE: Oh, my God.

12:44.247 --> 12:46.506
It seems the drinky-poo will
was in place

12:46.674 --> 12:47.748
at the time of the crash.

12:47.917 --> 12:50.676
"Always together makes
a family forever."

12:50.845 --> 12:53.605
-What a load of crap.
-What a hypocrite.

12:53.774 --> 12:54.831
Why didn't you stop this?

12:55.000 --> 12:56.590
I never knew about the kids!

12:56.759 --> 12:58.092
(exhales sharply)

12:58.261 --> 13:01.671
He did fess up about
that whore in Vegas.

13:01.840 --> 13:03.430
I was so mad,

13:03.599 --> 13:06.767
we slept in separate bedrooms
for six months,

13:06.936 --> 13:08.620
and he only got handies
for six more.

13:08.789 --> 13:10.271
-Oh, Mama!
-ERIC: Okay, Mom.

13:10.439 --> 13:12.123
This can't be legal,
especially if he was drunk.

13:12.350 --> 13:13.625
I've dealt with
a lot of bastards

13:13.794 --> 13:14.942
to get where I am.

13:15.111 --> 13:17.253
These three will be
no different.

13:18.706 --> 13:20.690
Eric, Reverend Thomas
mustn't find out

13:20.859 --> 13:21.966
about this, or Becky.

13:22.193 --> 13:24.636
You want me to lie
to my wife?

13:24.805 --> 13:27.547
-I'm not Dad.
-If they find out,

13:27.715 --> 13:29.516
it's over.

13:30.793 --> 13:32.626
Well, who the hell
are these people?

13:32.795 --> 13:33.812
<i> SINGER: ♪ Somebody gotta ♪</i>

13:33.980 --> 13:36.630
<i> ♪ Gotta raise a little hell ♪</i>

13:36.799 --> 13:38.541
<i> ♪ Whoa ♪</i>

13:38.634 --> 13:39.651
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:39.820 --> 13:41.486
<i> ♪ Whoa ♪</i>

13:41.655 --> 13:42.728
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:42.897 --> 13:44.656
<i> ♪ Whoa ♪</i>

13:44.825 --> 13:47.884
<i> (Dorothy's "Raise Hell")</i>

13:48.053 --> 13:51.404
<i> ♪ Somebody gotta,</i>
<i> gotta raise a little hell ♪</i>

13:51.573 --> 13:53.739
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

13:53.908 --> 13:54.891
(kid mumbles)

13:55.060 --> 13:57.168
(elevator door dings)

14:02.917 --> 14:03.824
-(elevator door dings)
-Which floor?

14:03.993 --> 14:05.826
-Same.
-That's good.

14:05.920 --> 14:08.071
-ANTONIO: Bro, do you mind?
-Sure.

14:08.239 --> 14:09.906
-Knock yourself out, man.
-No, dude.

14:10.075 --> 14:12.016
Don't smoke that
in front of my kid.

14:12.243 --> 14:14.185
Of course I'm not
the only one.

14:14.354 --> 14:15.928
I'm Ginger.

14:16.097 --> 14:17.838
Apparently I'm your sister.

14:17.932 --> 14:20.766
<i> (quirky music)</i>

14:20.861 --> 14:23.010
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:23.179 --> 14:26.180
My name is Franklin Lee,
in-house counsel,

14:26.349 --> 14:28.441
and I'll need your letters
and your IDs.

14:28.610 --> 14:33.997
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

14:35.433 --> 14:38.859
You must be Ginger,
Antonio, and, uh, Jason.

14:39.028 --> 14:40.712
Well, who's this little cherub?

14:40.881 --> 14:42.046
ANTONIO:
This is my son, Jesus.

14:42.215 --> 14:43.789
MARGARET:
Oh, if only somebody

14:43.958 --> 14:45.274
could bottle up the smell

14:45.443 --> 14:46.776
of little babies.

14:46.869 --> 14:49.387
If anybody could have,
it would have been Eugene.

14:49.614 --> 14:50.722
Well, all right, then.

14:50.891 --> 14:53.374
These are my children,
Rose and Eric.

14:53.542 --> 14:54.726
Rose?

14:54.895 --> 14:56.060
ERIC: I'm the senior VP
of operations,

14:56.287 --> 14:58.471
at least until
the dust settles,

14:58.565 --> 15:00.064
and, uh, you know,
from my perspective,

15:00.291 --> 15:02.734
there's no way I'm giving
a single piece

15:02.903 --> 15:04.477
of my family company
to a hooker...

15:04.571 --> 15:05.628
-Hm?
-ERIC: A hoodlum,

15:05.797 --> 15:07.054
and a drug dealer.

15:07.223 --> 15:07.906
Yo, I'm gonna knock
your teeth in, homie.

15:08.074 --> 15:10.391
This is my humming bird cake.

15:10.485 --> 15:13.819
I made it myself this morning
especially for y'all.

15:13.988 --> 15:16.639
(chuckles)
Back up.

15:16.732 --> 15:17.731
I'm not a hooker.

15:17.900 --> 15:19.325
You're not, huh?

15:19.494 --> 15:20.752
Yeah, I pulled up Sin Wagon
on my laptop.

15:20.921 --> 15:23.312
Nuns, milk maids,
farm girls,

15:23.481 --> 15:25.982
doing the most despicable,
disgusting things.

15:26.151 --> 15:28.635
So you subscribe
to our premium package?

15:30.989 --> 15:32.672
-Jason, you want some tea?
-You know what?

15:32.766 --> 15:33.914
I'm okay.

15:34.083 --> 15:35.825
Oh, she won't stop asking
until you say yes.

15:35.994 --> 15:38.327
-It's what she does.
-I'd love some.

15:38.496 --> 15:39.938
MARGARET: Rose.

15:40.106 --> 15:43.849
It was, uh, quite a surprise
that all of you

15:44.018 --> 15:45.851
were in Eugene's will.

15:45.946 --> 15:47.503
One which we are prepared
to contest, by the way.

15:47.596 --> 15:48.613
-There's a--
-MARGARET: But in fairness

15:48.782 --> 15:49.781
and sensitivity,

15:49.950 --> 15:54.177
we are prepared
to make an offer.

15:54.345 --> 15:56.696
FRANKLIN: Contingent
on the results of DNA tests

15:56.864 --> 15:58.681
and in signing
a non-disclosure agreement,

15:58.850 --> 16:00.291
each of you

16:00.460 --> 16:02.276
will receive $1 million.

16:02.370 --> 16:05.112
MARGARET:
I hope you enjoy my cake,

16:05.281 --> 16:08.115
after you provide your saliva,
of course.

16:08.284 --> 16:11.360
I grew up dirt poor knowing
Eugene Monreaux was my father.

16:11.529 --> 16:13.879
Y'all built this place

16:14.048 --> 16:16.123
on the back of a secret
I kept for you.

16:16.292 --> 16:18.868
I'm not walking away
for a million bucks.

16:19.037 --> 16:21.795
You're valued at 2.2 billion.

16:21.889 --> 16:22.981
And you flew us coach?

16:23.149 --> 16:25.650
I'm gonna need to talk
this over with my brothers

16:25.819 --> 16:26.967
and we'll get back to you.

16:27.136 --> 16:28.169
You take all
the time you need,

16:28.304 --> 16:30.379
but for the financial wellbeing

16:30.548 --> 16:33.049
of the company,
your discretion is required.

16:33.218 --> 16:34.900
We wouldn't want anyone
finding this out

16:35.069 --> 16:36.661
and nor should you.

16:36.830 --> 16:38.812
Well, that's all for now.

16:38.981 --> 16:40.647
Please spit.

16:40.742 --> 16:43.501
<i> (quirky music)</i>

16:43.728 --> 16:44.910
GINGER:
In my line of work,

16:45.079 --> 16:46.653
I've learned that
a desperate person

16:46.748 --> 16:48.581
will pay anything.

16:48.750 --> 16:49.632
(spits)

16:51.903 --> 16:55.404
Thank you for the lovely cake,
Mrs. Monreaux.

16:55.573 --> 16:57.423
Oh, you're welcome.

16:57.592 --> 17:01.927
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

17:02.096 --> 17:03.837
Maybe we should have
some sort

17:04.006 --> 17:05.857
of relationship with them.

17:06.026 --> 17:07.250
I mean, I don't know,
if Dad thought

17:07.343 --> 17:09.360
-putting them in the--
-Can it, Rose.

17:09.587 --> 17:10.920
(exhales)

17:11.089 --> 17:12.421
THOMAS:
How'd that go?

17:12.590 --> 17:14.774
How'd what go?

17:14.868 --> 17:16.534
You told Becky.

17:16.761 --> 17:18.928
ERIC:
She's my wife, Mom.

17:19.097 --> 17:19.929
Yeah.

17:20.098 --> 17:21.931
THOMAS:
We have bigger fish to fry.

17:22.100 --> 17:23.949
The network is falling apart.

17:24.044 --> 17:25.025
The business of the network

17:25.194 --> 17:27.436
is none of your concern,
Preacher.

17:27.605 --> 17:28.938
You are the talent.

17:29.031 --> 17:30.715
Well, thank you, Franklin,
for acknowledging that.

17:30.942 --> 17:32.550
So here's the plan.

17:32.719 --> 17:34.886
You need to get back on air.

17:35.055 --> 17:37.963
People watch<i> Sunshine</i>
for two reasons: you and me.

17:38.132 --> 17:40.040
Without you,
I suffer.

17:40.209 --> 17:42.618
No one should be made
to suffer.

17:42.787 --> 17:46.380
So you make Eric the CEO.

17:46.549 --> 17:48.882
I will serve in official
advisory capacity

17:49.051 --> 17:50.810
just as Eugene wanted,

17:50.978 --> 17:52.904
and you go back to doing
what you do best:

17:53.131 --> 17:55.648
recipes and advice.

17:55.817 --> 17:58.968
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

17:59.061 --> 18:01.153
Eric,
should we grab that lunch?

18:01.322 --> 18:06.826
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:06.994 --> 18:09.170
(door closes)

18:10.648 --> 18:13.499
<i> (jazzy music playing)</i>

18:13.668 --> 18:15.818
Margaret really hooked us up.

18:15.987 --> 18:17.002
Yeah.

18:17.097 --> 18:19.004
LUKE: Place has been energized
with fresh faces

18:19.173 --> 18:21.340
since the patriarch passed.

18:21.509 --> 18:22.658
Excuse me?

18:22.827 --> 18:25.419
Luke Taylor,
<i> Daily Edge.</i>

18:25.588 --> 18:26.437
Reporter?

18:26.606 --> 18:27.588
Well, my mother prefers

18:27.756 --> 18:28.922
investigative journalist.

18:29.016 --> 18:31.425
Rolls off the tongue nice,
right?

18:31.594 --> 18:33.093
You mind if I ask what business
you had today

18:33.262 --> 18:34.353
at Monreaux Unlimited?

18:34.522 --> 18:36.930
BELLMAN: Sir, I'm gonna have
to ask you to leave.

18:37.099 --> 18:38.432
No press allowed.

18:38.601 --> 18:41.677
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:41.770 --> 18:43.362
You should call me.

18:43.531 --> 18:49.869
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

18:49.963 --> 18:53.131
<i> (upbeat music playing)</i>

18:53.299 --> 18:55.550
(food sizzling)

18:57.119 --> 18:58.803
GINGER: Dude, they're loaded.
What are you talking about?

18:59.030 --> 19:02.140
I could train full time
and have child care for Jesus.

19:02.308 --> 19:06.293
Man, Eugene knew about you
and he let you struggle.

19:06.387 --> 19:09.038
Look, all I know
is one minute I'm broke,

19:09.207 --> 19:10.815
sweating my ass off in Queens,

19:10.984 --> 19:12.875
and the next minute
some white lady

19:13.044 --> 19:14.801
is offering me
a very delicious piece of cake

19:14.970 --> 19:16.136
and a million bucks.

19:16.230 --> 19:18.230
I'm good with both
those things.

19:18.399 --> 19:20.883
And I bet this is
the first time in your life

19:21.052 --> 19:22.067
that you've got real power.

19:22.236 --> 19:24.904
Not strength or muscle,
but power.

19:24.998 --> 19:26.405
-Don't you see that?
-Listen.

19:26.574 --> 19:27.573
I'm taking the money.

19:27.667 --> 19:29.408
Antonio,
I'm asking you to fight.

19:29.577 --> 19:31.243
When was the last time people
like us came out on top?

19:31.337 --> 19:33.171
People like what?

19:33.339 --> 19:35.173
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:35.341 --> 19:37.249
Is that what you're
gonna teach your son?

19:37.343 --> 19:38.509
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:38.736 --> 19:40.344
What about those DNA tests?

19:40.546 --> 19:43.664
Positive, except Jason's sample
was contaminated.

19:43.758 --> 19:45.141
He's retaking his.

19:50.748 --> 19:52.190
I am so proud of you.

19:52.417 --> 19:55.251
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

19:55.344 --> 19:56.769
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

19:56.938 --> 19:59.088
NORAH: Live from
the Sunshine Studios

19:59.257 --> 20:02.591
in beautiful New Orleans,
ladies and gentlemen,

20:02.760 --> 20:05.852
once again,
Margaret Monreaux.

20:06.021 --> 20:09.040
(cheers and applause)

20:09.209 --> 20:13.619
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

20:13.788 --> 20:14.954
MARGARET: Thank you.

20:15.122 --> 20:19.217
Thank you all so much
for that warm welcome home.

20:20.445 --> 20:21.886
One month ago,

20:22.113 --> 20:25.556
I lost my beloved husband
and best friend.

20:25.816 --> 20:28.968
I miss him greatly,
and truthfully,

20:29.136 --> 20:30.636
I didn't know if I could go on.

20:30.805 --> 20:31.971
<i> (somber music)</i>

20:32.139 --> 20:36.567
Then I thought of one
of Eugene's favorite verses.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.644
"Be watchful.

20:38.813 --> 20:40.887
<i> "Stand firm in your faith.</i>

20:41.056 --> 20:42.907
<i> Act like men.</i>
<i> Be strong."</i>

20:43.134 --> 20:44.725
(machine beeping)

20:44.819 --> 20:46.969
<i> Because of Eugene,</i>

20:47.138 --> 20:48.562
<i> because of your faith</i>
<i> in our mission,</i>

20:48.731 --> 20:50.539
<i> I'm back here today...</i>

20:52.493 --> 20:55.086
<i> Because we have work to do</i>
<i> in our great country.</i>

20:55.255 --> 20:57.813
<i> People like us,</i>
<i> people of faith,</i>

20:57.906 --> 20:59.924
<i> we are under constant attack,</i>

21:00.093 --> 21:01.484
<i> and now more than ever,</i>

21:01.652 --> 21:07.414
<i> I realize we must all stay</i>
<i> close to our families</i>

21:07.583 --> 21:10.017
<i> and keep them safe.</i>

21:11.253 --> 21:12.845
<i> That's what Eugene</i>
<i> would have wanted,</i>

21:12.939 --> 21:14.847
<i> both at home</i>

21:15.016 --> 21:18.000
<i>and right here with the family</i>
<i>we have in this room.</i>

21:18.093 --> 21:20.945
Always together makes
a family forever.

21:22.431 --> 21:24.949
<i> And family is the most</i>
<i> valuable thing in the world.</i>

21:25.118 --> 21:27.118
<i> (cheers and applause)</i>

21:27.287 --> 21:29.287
And that's why
we're not walking away

21:29.455 --> 21:30.663
for a million bucks.

21:35.353 --> 21:38.037
FRANKLIN: All of the other kids
have refused our offer.

21:38.131 --> 21:39.705
MARGARET: It's Ginger.
(groans)

21:39.874 --> 21:40.781
FRANKLIN: Can you blame them
for wanting

21:40.875 --> 21:43.025
a proper seat at the table?

21:43.194 --> 21:44.618
MARGARET: You sound like
you're on her side.

21:44.787 --> 21:46.137
I'm on my side, Margaret.

21:46.306 --> 21:48.047
I love you
but I got a lot to lose

21:48.141 --> 21:50.123
-if this company goes belly up.
-I know that.

21:50.292 --> 21:51.550
I got the place
in Pebble Beach.

21:51.719 --> 21:53.052
You got the loft in SoHo.

21:53.146 --> 21:54.979
Now, you know I like
my real estate, Margaret.

21:55.148 --> 21:56.705
-I said I know.
-(dogs barking)

21:56.874 --> 21:58.557
Just saying,

21:58.651 --> 22:02.636
taking a moment to look at it
from her side, okay?

22:02.805 --> 22:06.473
That will keep us from being
helpless in the negotiation.

22:06.642 --> 22:08.642
The only time a Monreaux girl
is helpless

22:08.811 --> 22:10.477
is when her nails are drying.

22:10.646 --> 22:12.496
If Ginger wants a proper seat
at the table,

22:12.665 --> 22:15.166
-let's give her one.
-(horse brays)

22:15.393 --> 22:17.317
I think a ladies luncheon
would be of great benefit

22:17.486 --> 22:18.669
to Miss Sweet.

22:18.838 --> 22:20.821
Oh, Madge, darling,

22:20.989 --> 22:22.155
-you just look wonderful.
-Oh.

22:22.358 --> 22:24.583
Did you get the chocolate
éclairs that I sent you?

22:24.752 --> 22:26.827
They were Eugene's favorite.

22:26.995 --> 22:28.737
Oh, dear.
Who is that?

22:28.831 --> 22:30.239
<i> (sweeping orchestral music)</i>

22:30.350 --> 22:33.184
MARGARET: An acquaintance.
Excuse me.

22:33.353 --> 22:34.685
Of course.

22:34.912 --> 22:40.416
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:40.585 --> 22:43.435
Margaret, darling.

22:43.529 --> 22:46.030
Thank you for the invitation.

22:46.199 --> 22:47.423
You should feel stupid
right now,

22:47.592 --> 22:48.682
'cause I certainly don't.

22:48.851 --> 22:50.426
Why, you wore my color.

22:50.553 --> 22:52.370
(Rose chuckles)

22:52.597 --> 22:56.448
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

22:56.617 --> 22:58.100
(Rose chuckles)

22:58.193 --> 23:00.936
Where did you get that outfit
on such short notice?

23:01.029 --> 23:04.548
-A friend sent it overnight.
-I love it.

23:04.717 --> 23:05.866
GINGER: Well, I love
what you're wearing.

23:05.960 --> 23:07.793
-You make that, too?
-ROSE: Uh-huh.

23:07.962 --> 23:09.053
I have a whole line planned,

23:09.222 --> 23:11.447
but somehow I'm not gaining
any traction on it.

23:11.616 --> 23:12.973
Excuse me.

23:14.710 --> 23:16.452
<i> Good afternoon, ladies,</i>

23:16.621 --> 23:19.455
and welcome to
our annual ladies luncheon.

23:19.624 --> 23:21.957
This year our focus is

23:22.050 --> 23:24.235
on the city's mentoring program
for girls,

23:24.462 --> 23:25.736
or as we prefer to call them,

23:25.905 --> 23:28.388
businesswomen of the future.

23:28.557 --> 23:31.057
It's been a sad time
at the network,

23:31.226 --> 23:33.802
so although I previously
agreed to speak today,

23:33.971 --> 23:35.562
I hope you'll understand
and forgive me

23:35.731 --> 23:38.157
if I do not,
but in my place,

23:38.251 --> 23:41.752
I'd like to introduce a woman
with a successful company

23:41.921 --> 23:44.422
that she built
from the ground up.

23:44.590 --> 23:48.426
The lovely lady
in that charming hoop skirt,

23:48.594 --> 23:50.261
Miss Ginger Sweet.

23:50.430 --> 23:52.430
(applause)

23:52.598 --> 23:53.931
Come on up here, Ginger!

23:54.100 --> 23:57.176
<i> (upbeat country music)</i>

23:57.344 --> 24:00.496
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:00.665 --> 24:02.422
Let's welcome Ginger.

24:02.591 --> 24:06.277
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:06.446 --> 24:08.854
Why don't you start by telling
these young ladies

24:08.948 --> 24:10.522
what you do for a living,
sweetie.

24:10.691 --> 24:12.116
Inspire them.

24:12.285 --> 24:14.577
I know how proud you are
of what you do.

24:19.517 --> 24:22.351
<i> (soft music)</i>

24:22.520 --> 24:24.203
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:24.297 --> 24:28.448
Well, it seems that Miss Sweet
has a bit of stage fright.

24:28.617 --> 24:29.875
We've all been there.

24:30.044 --> 24:31.952
Why don't we bring up
our next speaker

24:32.046 --> 24:33.637
and, uh, we'll get this
all sorted out?

24:33.806 --> 24:34.972
(chuckles)

24:35.141 --> 24:36.957
Come on over here, sweetie.

24:37.125 --> 24:40.035
There's no place for you
in civil society.

24:40.204 --> 24:42.554
I'm offering you
two million now,

24:42.648 --> 24:43.814
which we feel
is quite generous,

24:43.983 --> 24:45.874
considering you represent
no more than ten minutes

24:46.043 --> 24:47.467
of my husband's pleasure.

24:47.636 --> 24:49.545
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:49.714 --> 24:51.471
You take the money and go home.

24:51.640 --> 24:56.235
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

24:56.403 --> 24:58.829
Nothing makes me happier
than cooking for my boy.

24:58.998 --> 25:01.314
-Thanks for coming over.
-Aw. Wow.

25:01.408 --> 25:02.666
Mm-hmm.

25:02.835 --> 25:04.484
No, no, no.
None for me.

25:04.653 --> 25:05.561
Becky and I are off sugar.

25:05.730 --> 25:08.580
It's 100% pure
unfiltered maple.

25:08.749 --> 25:10.156
It's good for you.

25:10.325 --> 25:12.510
It's full of magnesium
and zinc and--

25:12.678 --> 25:13.677
All right,
all right.

25:13.904 --> 25:15.738
(chuckles)

25:15.906 --> 25:18.090
Why am I here?

25:18.184 --> 25:21.910
Well, I've thought about it
and I've prayed on it,

25:22.079 --> 25:24.188
and I don't think you're ready

25:24.357 --> 25:26.315
to take your father's place
in the company.

25:27.585 --> 25:29.935
Now, the world is watching
and we need

25:30.104 --> 25:32.696
to take things very slowly
for a beat.

25:32.865 --> 25:35.348
Slow?
No, why slow?

25:35.517 --> 25:36.516
The company needs
to take action

25:36.685 --> 25:37.868
to preserve its future now.

25:38.037 --> 25:43.290
Son, this may not feel like
a loving statement but...

25:45.936 --> 25:48.087
You lack polish.

25:49.531 --> 25:52.291
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

25:52.459 --> 25:56.036
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

25:56.130 --> 25:58.204
Maple syrup is still sugar,
Mama.

25:58.299 --> 26:00.057
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:00.284 --> 26:01.450
You can dress it up
all you like.

26:01.619 --> 26:03.394
It's still gonna kill you.

26:05.047 --> 26:07.790
Dad told the Reverend
he wanted me to take over.

26:07.958 --> 26:09.775
Why are you denying me?

26:11.053 --> 26:12.961
What, doesn't Dad get
a say in any of this,

26:13.013 --> 26:14.463
or have you already
forgotten him?

26:14.632 --> 26:15.631
(door opening)

26:15.800 --> 26:19.059
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:19.153 --> 26:21.320
Come on in, Franklin.
Mom's serving up sugar.

26:21.414 --> 26:25.324
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:25.492 --> 26:26.733
(door closes)

26:26.902 --> 26:30.162
Rumors starting to fly
about our hotel guests.

26:30.331 --> 26:32.548
Might be best to keep them
out of public view.

26:34.335 --> 26:35.759
We'll bring them out
to the camp.

26:35.928 --> 26:38.512
Let everybody simmer down
for a bit.

26:40.825 --> 26:42.582
It's time
to replace Eugene.

26:42.676 --> 26:44.509
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:44.678 --> 26:46.437
For the sake of the family.

26:46.606 --> 26:52.017
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

26:52.186 --> 26:54.353
Earl.
(dog tag jingling)

26:54.521 --> 26:55.946
(dog whining)

26:56.173 --> 26:58.523
This is for you, baby.

26:58.692 --> 26:59.858
-(TV playing indistinctly)
-Eric!

27:00.027 --> 27:01.619
<i> NEWSCASTER: For more</i>
<i> on this developing story,</i>

27:01.787 --> 27:03.028
<i> we take you live</i>
<i> to the company's headquarters</i>

27:03.197 --> 27:04.455
<i> -at downtown New Orleans...</i>
-ERIC: You all right?

27:04.624 --> 27:06.698
<i> NEWSCASTER: Where a news</i>
<i> conference is happening now.</i>

27:06.867 --> 27:09.351
<i> I would like</i>
<i> to assure our audience</i>

27:09.520 --> 27:11.444
<i> and our shareholders</i>
<i> that we are far</i>

27:11.613 --> 27:13.113
<i> from a rudderless ship.</i>

27:13.281 --> 27:15.707
<i> Monreaux Unlimited</i>
<i> will remain in the family</i>

27:15.876 --> 27:18.360
<i> in trusted,</i>
<i> responsible hands.</i>

27:18.529 --> 27:19.803
<i> Effective immediately,</i>

27:19.972 --> 27:21.972
<i> the new CEO</i>
<i> for Monreaux Unlimited</i>

27:22.141 --> 27:26.702
<i> will be Margaret Monreaux.</i>

27:26.871 --> 27:28.312
<i> MARGARET: Thank you.</i>

27:28.481 --> 27:30.555
<i> -(camera shutters clicking)</i>
<i> -Thank you all so much.</i>

27:30.724 --> 27:32.224
Your mom's a bitch.

27:32.393 --> 27:35.560
<i> MARGARET: I take this</i>
<i> responsibility seriously.</i>

27:35.729 --> 27:37.655
-Two million?
-Wow.

27:37.823 --> 27:39.573
-Well done.
-I'm not taking it.

27:41.643 --> 27:43.552
Why?

27:43.721 --> 27:44.995
I can see a loss
when it's coming.

27:45.164 --> 27:46.980
-(knocking at door)
-We're worth more.

27:47.149 --> 27:49.741
All of us are worth more.
They're trying to erase us.

27:49.943 --> 27:52.670
If I'm gonna be erased,
it's gonna cost her.

27:52.838 --> 27:53.912
Good morning.

27:54.081 --> 27:55.339
Mrs. Monreaux
has invited you all

27:55.508 --> 27:56.581
to stay at her hunting camp.

27:56.750 --> 27:57.824
So she can shoot us?

27:57.993 --> 28:00.160
ANTONIO: Yo, yo, look.

28:00.328 --> 28:02.905
You can stay here if you want,
but I'm going.

28:02.998 --> 28:04.423
Me, too.
I'm not worth more.

28:04.591 --> 28:06.408
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

28:06.501 --> 28:09.335
(car engine revving)

28:09.430 --> 28:10.762
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:10.931 --> 28:12.097
(car door opens, closes)

28:12.266 --> 28:13.190
ERIC: I can't believe
my own mother

28:13.359 --> 28:15.250
would take a job
from right underneath me!

28:15.419 --> 28:17.010
-I went to Wharton!
-You about flunked out.

28:17.104 --> 28:18.636
ERIC: You think the Reverend's
gonna be reassured

28:18.698 --> 28:19.604
with you at the helm?

28:19.773 --> 28:20.756
You watch that tongue,
young man.

28:20.849 --> 28:21.865
I created the network,

28:22.034 --> 28:24.517
I have the most-watched
lifestyle show on TV,

28:24.686 --> 28:25.610
and I am your mother.

28:25.779 --> 28:28.021
I will not tolerate disrespect.

28:28.190 --> 28:29.114
-(helicopter whirring)
-ROSE: Hey, Eric.

28:29.283 --> 28:30.766
Our sister and brothers
are here.

28:30.935 --> 28:33.618
They're staying with us.

28:33.787 --> 28:36.605
You have lost your damn mind!

28:36.698 --> 28:38.607
-(slap smacks)
-Oh.

28:38.700 --> 28:41.460
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

28:41.628 --> 28:43.512
(exhales sharply)

28:49.544 --> 28:52.788
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

28:52.957 --> 28:55.123
(door squeaking)

28:55.217 --> 28:57.067
MARGARET: Welcome to the camp.

28:57.236 --> 28:59.069
Make yourselves at home.
Take your shoes off.

28:59.296 --> 29:00.979
Oh, these are
my Tuesday socks,

29:01.148 --> 29:02.573
and it's Friday.
Are you sure?

29:02.742 --> 29:03.966
You got a point.
(laughs)

29:04.134 --> 29:05.650
I'll take my hat off, then.

29:05.819 --> 29:07.970
Antonio, I got you
a babysitter.

29:08.138 --> 29:09.654
Pick a room upstairs.
Any room.

29:09.823 --> 29:10.806
Any room?
Ah, thank you.

29:10.899 --> 29:11.807
Hey, let me show you around.

29:11.976 --> 29:13.083
-Okay.
-Come on, okay.

29:13.252 --> 29:15.310
So, this is
our, like, main...

29:15.403 --> 29:17.980
About lunch.
What I did was wrong.

29:18.148 --> 29:21.741
We're both strong-willed women
working through our emotions,

29:21.910 --> 29:24.002
and I'd like it
if we could start over.

29:24.096 --> 29:26.004
You really think I'm stupid,
don't you?

29:26.173 --> 29:29.007
No, definitely not, Ginger.

29:29.101 --> 29:30.826
I've learned never
to underestimate

29:30.995 --> 29:33.662
Eugene's progeny.

29:33.831 --> 29:35.347
Pick a room, Ginger.

29:35.516 --> 29:36.756
I'm cooking you all

29:36.925 --> 29:38.609
a traditional Cajun dinner
tonight.

29:40.446 --> 29:44.656
I know you probably have some
hard feelings towards Dad...

29:46.768 --> 29:50.195
But I think if you'd known him,
you would have liked him.

29:50.364 --> 29:52.623
-I don't know about that.
-Hmm.

29:52.792 --> 29:54.941
He was, like,
the only person

29:55.110 --> 29:57.669
who believed
in what I'm trying to do.

30:00.707 --> 30:02.691
You mind if I smoke
some weed?

30:02.784 --> 30:04.510
Just calms the nerves.

30:05.879 --> 30:07.554
What do you have
to be nervous about?

30:09.366 --> 30:11.308
(scoffs)

30:11.477 --> 30:12.810
I'm kidding.
(laughs)

30:12.978 --> 30:16.538
This entire situation would
turn anybody into a pot head.

30:16.707 --> 30:19.724
<i> SINGER: ♪ Never change, yeah,</i>
<i> just always the same ♪</i>

30:19.893 --> 30:23.177
<i> ♪ Whatever ya need ♪</i>

30:23.380 --> 30:24.563
Oh.

30:24.731 --> 30:26.931
<i>SINGER: ♪ And all you gotta do</i>
<i>is call ♪</i>

30:27.067 --> 30:29.734
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.

30:29.903 --> 30:31.495
I can't believe I did that.

30:31.664 --> 30:34.981
I'd like to clear the air
and apologize to you three

30:35.150 --> 30:37.984
for how I've conducted myself

30:38.153 --> 30:39.837
After much prayer
and reflection,

30:40.005 --> 30:44.416
I've decided to give each
of you 1%

30:44.510 --> 30:45.825
of the company.

30:45.994 --> 30:47.903
It is what Eugene wanted.

30:48.072 --> 30:51.590
All I ask is that you sign NDAs

30:51.758 --> 30:54.000
protecting the reputation

30:54.169 --> 30:55.744
of the company
and our interests in it.

30:55.913 --> 30:57.596
1% comes out to 6 million.

30:57.764 --> 30:58.763
Wow.

30:58.858 --> 31:00.415
-Thank you.
-No.

31:00.508 --> 31:03.843
Uh, Ginger, you do realize
that she's being really,

31:03.937 --> 31:05.529
really nice to us right now?

31:05.756 --> 31:06.697
MARGARET: Thank you, Antonio.

31:06.866 --> 31:08.607
JASON:
Personally, I wanna say

31:08.701 --> 31:10.759
I will take your offer
and go home

31:10.852 --> 31:13.612
and none of you
have to see me ever,

31:13.706 --> 31:15.021
ever again.
I totally promise.

31:15.190 --> 31:17.766
GINGER:
Given there are five of us

31:17.935 --> 31:19.935
including Eric and Rose,

31:20.104 --> 31:22.287
I think 5% is a better number.

31:22.381 --> 31:24.789
$30 million?

31:24.884 --> 31:27.109
And biblically speaking,

31:27.277 --> 31:29.869
the number five symbolizes
God's grace,

31:29.963 --> 31:33.039
goodness,
and favor toward humans.

31:33.208 --> 31:36.785
It's mentioned 318 times
in scripture.

31:36.878 --> 31:41.306
The ten commandments contain
two sets of five commandments.

31:41.475 --> 31:44.717
The first five commandments
are related to our treatment

31:44.886 --> 31:46.978
and relationship with God,

31:47.147 --> 31:49.055
and the last five commandments

31:49.224 --> 31:50.741
concern our relationship
with others,

31:50.968 --> 31:54.894
like me, Antonio,
Jason, Eric, and Rose.

31:55.063 --> 31:56.914
What do you think, Rose?

31:57.082 --> 31:58.248
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

31:58.417 --> 32:01.084
Is $30 million enough
to ghost this joint

32:01.253 --> 32:03.211
and start your own
fashion house?

32:04.815 --> 32:06.665
Yep.

32:06.833 --> 32:08.759
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:08.928 --> 32:11.820
You are a goddess.

32:11.913 --> 32:16.016
Just a complete
and total goddess.

32:16.843 --> 32:19.102
I wish I was more like you.

32:22.849 --> 32:25.108
You're more like me
than you know.

32:26.003 --> 32:27.852
I see you.

32:28.021 --> 32:30.781
I see a girl who spent
her whole life

32:30.950 --> 32:33.008
making sure her mom was okay

32:33.101 --> 32:37.079
before she even thought
to have a thought for herself.

32:39.866 --> 32:42.542
Tell me about your mom,
Ginger.

32:46.039 --> 32:48.423
Can you just keep telling me
how awesome I am?

32:49.617 --> 32:50.634
No prob.

32:52.029 --> 32:53.361
(knocking at door)

32:53.530 --> 32:55.389
(door opens)

32:57.868 --> 32:59.643
Despite what you may think,

32:59.812 --> 33:01.812
your father cared deeply
about you.

33:02.014 --> 33:04.039
You didn't know it,
but he followed your business.

33:04.208 --> 33:06.875
He didn't like it,
but he couldn't help

33:07.044 --> 33:09.027
but see a bit
of himself in you.

33:10.047 --> 33:12.322
He wrote this letter recently.

33:13.900 --> 33:15.075
(clears throat)

33:17.904 --> 33:20.288
Said he wasn't getting
any younger.

33:34.071 --> 33:36.404
<i> EUGENE: Dear Ginger,</i>

33:36.498 --> 33:40.909
<i>I want you to know that</i>
<i>I've thought of you every day.</i>

33:41.002 --> 33:43.836
<i> I'm proud of who you are</i>
<i> because you're not afraid</i>

33:44.005 --> 33:46.523
<i> to be who you are.</i>

33:46.692 --> 33:49.175
<i> I've always loved you.</i>

33:49.344 --> 33:52.195
<i> I wish I'd been</i>
<i> the father you deserved.</i>

33:54.591 --> 33:57.200
<i> (upbeat music)</i>

33:57.427 --> 33:59.444
<i> ERIC: Come on, church!</i>
<i> Put your hands together!</i>

33:59.613 --> 34:00.853
Hands together for the Lord!

34:01.022 --> 34:03.022
<i> ♪ Trying just to hold on ♪</i>

34:03.116 --> 34:05.784
<i> ♪ While the ground</i>
<i> keeps shaking ♪</i>

34:05.952 --> 34:10.047
<i>♪ But I'm never gonna question</i>
<i>who I place my faith in ♪</i>

34:10.215 --> 34:12.198
<i> ♪ No ♪</i>

34:12.367 --> 34:14.776
<i> ♪ No, no, no</i>
<i> 'cause He rose ♪</i>

34:14.869 --> 34:16.628
(cheering)

34:16.797 --> 34:17.779
(laughs)

34:17.948 --> 34:25.136
<i> ♪ Yeah He rose ♪</i>

34:25.305 --> 34:26.788
♪ ♪

34:26.957 --> 34:28.565
<i> ♪ Yeah He rose ♪</i>

34:28.734 --> 34:31.626
I love when he sings.

34:31.795 --> 34:32.644
Yeah.

34:32.813 --> 34:35.797
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:35.966 --> 34:37.449
<i> ERIC: ♪ Yeah ♪</i>

34:38.893 --> 34:41.912
<i> -♪ 'Cause he rose ♪</i>
<i> -Whoo!</i>

34:42.081 --> 34:43.896
<i> Hands together for the Lord.</i>
<i> He's alive forever.</i>

34:44.065 --> 34:45.916
For Tuesday's
cooking segment,

34:46.143 --> 34:49.994
how about deep fried ham cheese
basil sandwiches?

34:50.163 --> 34:51.737
The spirit comes into a man's
heart when he is in need,

34:51.906 --> 34:53.982
and the Spirit says,
"Lay it all unto me."

34:54.151 --> 34:56.593
Brother Eric,
unburden your heart.

34:58.004 --> 34:59.078
Thank you, Reverend.

34:59.247 --> 35:02.265
Um, yeah, my heart is, uh--
my heart's heavy

35:02.492 --> 35:06.269
<i> and full of grief</i>
<i> for myself and my family,</i>

35:06.438 --> 35:09.106
<i> uh, for I fear</i>
<i> that we've lost our way.</i>

35:09.274 --> 35:10.999
<i> Speak the truth, all right?</i>

35:11.092 --> 35:14.111
<i>-God's listening.</i>
<i>-Unburden your heart, brother.</i>

35:15.172 --> 35:17.505
<i> ERIC: So my father, Eugene,</i>

35:17.674 --> 35:19.023
<i> um, the man that--</i>

35:19.192 --> 35:23.936
<i>that you all knew and loved...</i>

35:24.105 --> 35:25.680
-Oh!
<i> -Unbeknownst to us,</i>

35:25.849 --> 35:26.865
<i> -he had three--</i>
-(grunts)

35:27.033 --> 35:30.943
<i> Matthew 26:15 asks,</i>

35:31.037 --> 35:32.854
<i> "What are you willing</i>
<i> to give me</i>

35:33.023 --> 35:34.947
<i>if I deliver Him over to you?"</i>

35:35.041 --> 35:37.876
<i> Now, there are a lot</i>
<i> of businesses out there</i>

35:38.044 --> 35:40.028
<i> who take far more</i>
<i> than they give</i>

35:40.197 --> 35:41.754
<i> when it comes to deliveries.</i>

35:41.807 --> 35:43.807
<i> They say vote</i>
<i> with your dollar.</i>

35:43.976 --> 35:45.809
<i> Well, I say pray</i>
<i> with your dollar.</i>

35:46.069 --> 35:48.036
Reverend,
can I have a word?

35:48.205 --> 35:51.039
<i> I give you Sunny Club.</i>
Hello, everybody.

35:51.132 --> 35:52.315
<i> Now, Sunny Club</i>
<i> is an online fellowship...</i>

35:52.484 --> 35:53.650
I see what you're doing.

35:53.877 --> 35:55.134
You will lose.
You hear me?

35:55.303 --> 35:56.895
You put Eric in charge
or the world hears the truth.

35:57.063 --> 35:58.971
You were preaching
inside a double-wide

35:59.140 --> 36:01.049
when I found you.
I created you.

36:01.218 --> 36:03.827
-You don't scare me.
-Well, maybe I should.

36:04.054 --> 36:07.739
Can you hear me in Hong Kong?
From Norway to LA?

36:07.908 --> 36:09.891
-Can you hear me in Australia?
-(chuckles)

36:10.060 --> 36:12.060
The San Francisco Bay?

36:12.229 --> 36:13.912
You'll be lucky
if they can hear you

36:14.006 --> 36:15.172
in Luling, Louisiana
after this.

36:15.399 --> 36:16.581
You're out of your depth,
CEO.

36:16.750 --> 36:18.066
You get rid of me,

36:18.159 --> 36:19.676
you lose all your precious
Sunny Club customers.

36:19.903 --> 36:20.844
Who'll be left
to buy your toilet paper

36:21.013 --> 36:22.012
and your greeting cards?

36:22.181 --> 36:23.996
You might even have
to sell Butt Butter.

36:24.165 --> 36:24.848
<i> MARGARET: Simply sign up...</i>

36:25.017 --> 36:27.091
Excuse me.
I have a show to do.

36:27.260 --> 36:28.834
<i> Praise Cart and behold...</i>

36:29.003 --> 36:30.520
-Norah!
<i> -They're coming soon.</i>

36:32.249 --> 36:35.099
THOMAS:
Today's sermon is Luke 8:17.

36:35.194 --> 36:37.694
"For nothing is hidden that
will not become evident

36:37.863 --> 36:40.772
when come to light."
Eric?

36:40.866 --> 36:44.259
<i> (dramatic music)</i>

36:44.428 --> 36:46.852
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

36:47.021 --> 36:50.189
(crowd murmuring)

36:50.358 --> 36:51.958
(clears throat)

36:53.437 --> 36:56.621
We all have secrets.

36:56.715 --> 36:57.881
Don't we?

36:58.050 --> 37:00.175
(cell phone ringing)

37:01.869 --> 37:04.612
-Hi.
<i> -TINA: Hey, baby doll.</i>

37:04.781 --> 37:06.965
Rachel and I were just thinking
about how much we missed you.

37:07.133 --> 37:08.800
-Hi.
-How's it going down there?

37:08.894 --> 37:11.135
Well, you're not going
to believe it,

37:11.304 --> 37:14.898
but I am staying at their house
in the country.

37:15.125 --> 37:16.474
Of course you are.

37:16.643 --> 37:18.884
-(sighs) I bet it's huge.
-Hey, I wanna talk to her.

37:19.053 --> 37:20.737
Honey, when are you gonna
come back, huh?

37:20.906 --> 37:22.072
Tina, give it.
Let me talk to her.

37:22.241 --> 37:25.133
<i>TINA: All right, Rachel</i>
<i>wants to say something to you.</i>

37:25.226 --> 37:26.985
<i> RACHEL: Hey, did you</i>
<i> not get my text?</i>

37:27.079 --> 37:29.079
Yeah, I just--I haven't
had time to--

37:29.306 --> 37:31.639
Big Sally poached
Sheila and Kitty.

37:31.808 --> 37:32.916
I have been
at the mall recruiting

37:33.143 --> 37:33.975
for, like, four straight days.

37:34.144 --> 37:35.994
Hmm?
Yeah, I'm listening.

37:36.162 --> 37:37.645
Okay, let's just talk
about it later.

37:37.814 --> 37:38.738
Obviously, you're busy there.

37:38.906 --> 37:40.648
<i> -GINGER: I'm sorry, Rach.</i>
-Mm.

37:40.817 --> 37:42.667
Yeah.
You're fine.

37:42.836 --> 37:45.336
<i> GINGER: It's just--</i>
<i> don't tell Mom--</i>

37:45.505 --> 37:48.080
but...

37:48.249 --> 37:50.008
I'm starting to like
these people.

37:50.176 --> 37:55.588
Eugene wrote me a letter.

37:55.757 --> 37:58.516
<i> (soft dramatic music)</i>

37:58.685 --> 38:04.339
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:04.466 --> 38:05.690
(door opens)

38:05.784 --> 38:10.102
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:10.271 --> 38:12.938
GINGER: I have a question
about my father.

38:13.033 --> 38:14.624
Hello, honey.
I didn't see you there.

38:14.793 --> 38:18.202
I'm a lefty.

38:18.297 --> 38:19.779
My mom told me that
I got that from Eugene.

38:19.947 --> 38:21.873
Is that true?

38:22.042 --> 38:23.616
Is everything all right,
sweetie?

38:23.785 --> 38:26.361
A right-handed person
wrote this.

38:26.530 --> 38:28.046
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:28.140 --> 38:31.266
Eugene didn't feel this way
about me, did he?

38:32.869 --> 38:34.436
Did you fake this?

38:36.206 --> 38:38.315
What kind of person does that?

38:40.544 --> 38:42.193
(exhales sharply)
I...

38:43.730 --> 38:45.822
Uh, I don't know what to say.

38:46.033 --> 38:48.283
I don't want your money.

38:49.069 --> 38:51.310
Or your disgusting family.

38:51.479 --> 38:53.145
You know, maybe someday

38:53.314 --> 38:54.980
you'll be as good
as you think you are,

38:55.149 --> 38:58.442
and just so you know,

38:58.578 --> 39:02.172
Eugene spent more than
ten minutes with my mother.

39:04.158 --> 39:06.401
They were together for a year.

39:06.494 --> 39:13.308
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:21.418 --> 39:22.417
(zipper zipping)

39:22.586 --> 39:24.936
<i> (dramatic country music)</i>

39:25.105 --> 39:26.512
Jason and I
are taking the deal.

39:26.681 --> 39:29.014
Fine.
Take their money.

39:29.067 --> 39:32.443
Make sure you get it
while they still have it.

39:32.612 --> 39:34.445
Don't mess this up for me.

39:34.614 --> 39:40.460
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

39:43.698 --> 39:46.124
I am struggling, Lord.

39:46.218 --> 39:51.370
I am struggling to understand
your will for me.

39:51.539 --> 39:53.798
Show me the way.

39:53.892 --> 39:55.708
I will follow.

39:55.877 --> 39:59.229
(baby cooing)

39:59.398 --> 40:04.049
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:04.252 --> 40:07.311
I'm so sorry.
He--he got away from me.

40:07.406 --> 40:09.464
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:09.633 --> 40:14.302
Um, Miss Monreaux, I, uh--
I just wanted to say thanks.

40:14.471 --> 40:16.061
For everything.

40:16.230 --> 40:18.489
You're gonna change
my little boy's life.

40:18.658 --> 40:21.492
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:21.661 --> 40:23.311
Have you thought
about education?

40:23.480 --> 40:26.256
You--you have
to get on that right now.

40:26.425 --> 40:29.241
There are some amazing schools
in New Orleans.

40:29.410 --> 40:31.577
You should discuss it
with his mother.

40:31.746 --> 40:34.305
She's not really
in the picture.

40:35.750 --> 40:37.508
Oh.

40:37.677 --> 40:39.269
ANTONIO:
Miss Monreaux,

40:39.438 --> 40:41.420
I wanted you to know that
Ginger's been talking

40:41.589 --> 40:43.347
to the press.

40:43.442 --> 40:49.988
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:51.174 --> 40:52.097
LUKE: Did you get my message?

40:52.266 --> 40:53.174
GINGER: Are they ready for me?

40:53.343 --> 40:55.100
Yes, full house,
but we got a problem.

40:55.269 --> 40:57.454
What's the issue?
I gave you the exclusive.

40:57.622 --> 40:58.696
We had a deal.

40:58.790 --> 41:02.350
Yeah, but my boss just made
a different one.

41:02.443 --> 41:03.609
Ginger, don't go!

41:03.778 --> 41:05.203
MARGARET:
Ladies and gentlemen,

41:05.371 --> 41:08.690
I thank you for coming together
on such short notice.

41:08.858 --> 41:10.800
In the past few days,

41:10.969 --> 41:12.618
it has become abundantly clear

41:12.787 --> 41:15.454
that I cannot
do this job alone.

41:15.548 --> 41:17.532
Congratulations, CEO.

41:17.701 --> 41:19.033
(exhales)

41:19.202 --> 41:21.928
Now with the passing of Eugene,

41:21.980 --> 41:26.224
we lost our CEO,
I lost my husband,

41:26.392 --> 41:30.653
and Rose and Eric lost
their father.

41:30.822 --> 41:33.490
But we have gained as well.

41:33.658 --> 41:35.216
Unbeknownst to us,

41:35.385 --> 41:38.736
Eugene had fathered
three other children.

41:38.830 --> 41:39.904
(crowd murmuring)

41:40.073 --> 41:41.831
And they're here with us today.

41:42.058 --> 41:45.484
God, he sees all,

41:45.653 --> 41:47.170
and he forgives all.

41:47.339 --> 41:49.564
-Eugene. (chuckles)
-(mutters)

41:49.733 --> 41:51.582
We all know that
he had his demons.

41:51.751 --> 41:54.861
We all do,
and so I forgive him.

41:54.996 --> 41:58.589
And Reverend Thomas,
he forgives him.

41:58.800 --> 42:00.850
Oh, now that's
true Christianity.

42:01.077 --> 42:03.244
Judge not lest ye be judged.

42:03.413 --> 42:04.687
That's what the Reverend
told me,

42:04.856 --> 42:06.414
and he got us through this.

42:06.583 --> 42:08.249
Thank you, Paul.

42:08.342 --> 42:11.194
God decides who comes
into your life,

42:11.363 --> 42:14.697
but your heart must decide
who stays,

42:14.866 --> 42:16.849
so with the Lord's guidance,

42:17.018 --> 42:20.762
I welcome Antonio Rivera,
Jason Conley,

42:20.930 --> 42:22.855
and Ginger Sweet to ours.

42:23.024 --> 42:25.600
<i> (country music)</i>

42:25.769 --> 42:28.527
Hey, Jason, where--
where you going?

42:28.696 --> 42:30.438
He's a camera-shy cutie.

42:30.607 --> 42:32.774
Ginger, get on up here.

42:32.942 --> 42:34.425
I know you're not shy.

42:38.464 --> 42:40.464
(camera shutter clicks)

42:40.633 --> 42:42.058
Did you really think you'd have

42:42.285 --> 42:43.618
the upper hand
with the press in my town?

42:43.787 --> 42:47.638
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:47.807 --> 42:49.381
What in Heaven's name is that?

42:49.550 --> 42:52.810
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

42:52.904 --> 42:54.478
That's my mother.

42:54.647 --> 43:01.452
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:09.662 --> 43:12.571
<i> (suspenseful music)</i>

43:12.740 --> 43:15.699
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:15.835 --> 43:19.262
(gasping)

43:21.582 --> 43:23.582
Is this Hell?

43:23.676 --> 43:26.251
No, Louisiana.

43:26.346 --> 43:29.314
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

43:36.597 --> 43:37.614
<i> (upbeat country music)</i>

43:37.782 --> 43:39.507
<i> SINGER: ♪ Gold coin ♪</i>

43:39.676 --> 43:41.767
<i> ♪ Stacks on stacks ♪</i>

43:41.936 --> 43:42.844
<i> ♪ Make 'em write that check ♪</i>

43:43.012 --> 43:45.455
<i> ♪ I want hard cash ♪</i>

43:45.624 --> 43:46.956
<i> ♪ Greenback ♪</i>

43:47.183 --> 43:48.941
<i> (sings indistinctly)</i>

43:49.110 --> 43:50.685
<i> ♪ Oh, that's a fact ♪</i>

43:50.854 --> 43:52.703
<i> ♪ I got the right class ♪</i>

43:52.872 --> 43:55.039
<i> ♪ Yo, what's her weight ♪</i>

43:55.133 --> 43:56.966
<i> ♪ Rubies, rubies,</i>
<i> yin and yang ♪</i>

43:57.193 --> 43:58.876
<i> ♪ Pounds on pounds</i>
<i> in Swiss banks ♪</i>

43:59.045 --> 44:00.970
<i> ♪ That's the language</i>
<i> that I speak ♪</i>

44:01.197 --> 44:02.788
<i>♪ Now I lay me down to sleep ♪</i>

44:02.957 --> 44:04.223
<i> ♪ Amen ♪</i>

44:09.706 --> 44:12.723
Captioned by Captionmax
